'''Prince Kwabena Adu''' (born 23 September 2003) is a Ghanaian [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]] and the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]]. He was included in [[The Guardian]]'s "Next Generation 2020".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2020/oct/08/next-generation-2020-60-of-the-best-young-talents-in-world-football |title=Next Generation 2020: 60 of the best young talents in world football |date=8 October 2020 |accessdate=9 October 2020 |work=The Guardian}}</ref>

==Career==
On 1 September 2023, Kwabena Adu joined [[Ukrainian Premier League]] club [[FC Kryvbas Kryvyi Rih (2020)|Kryvbas Kryvyi Rih]] on a free transfer and signed a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |title=Ukrainian club Kryvbas Kryvyi Rih announce signing of Ghanaian duo Konadu Yiadom and Prince Kwabena Adu |url=https://ghanasoccernet.com/ukrainian-club-kryvbas-kryvyi-rih-announce-signing-of-ghanaian-duo-konadu-yiadom-and-prince-kwabena-adu |website=Ghana Soccer Net |publisher=Ghana Soccer Net |access-date=30 January 2025 |ref=4}}</ref>

On 28 August 2024, Kwabena Adu signed a three-year contract with [[Czech First League]] club [[FC Viktoria Plzeň|Viktoria Plzeň]].<ref>{{cite press release|url=https://www.fcviktoria.cz/clanek.asp?id=Kralovna-ma-sveho-prince-Do-Viktorie-prichazi-Prince-Adu-z-Kryvbasu-16847 |title=Královna má svého prince! Do Viktorie přichází Prince Adu z Kryvbasu |date=28 August 2024 |accessdate=28 August 2024 |work=[[FC Viktoria Plzeň]]|language=cs}}</ref>

==International career==
Adu was called up to the [[Ghana national football team|Ghana national team]] for a set of friendly matches in November 2025.<ref>{{cite web|first=Owuraku|last=Ampofo|title=Otto Addo names 22-man Ghana squad for friendlies against Japan and South Korea|url=https://www.flashscore.com/news/soccer-kirin-cup-japan-otto-addo-names-22-man-ghana-squad-for-friendlies-against-japan-and-south-korea/8dKZmxwh/|website=FlashScore.com|date=11 November 2025|access-date=12 November 2025}}</ref>

